{
  "stem": "2581.3",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "As I got up to bring something to the table-- I don't remember, salt or whatever it was-- I see there's a third potato in my plate-- in my bowl.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I screamed at my father like never before.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I wanted that potato so badly, but yet I felt the respect for my father, that he has to have it and it was going back and forth, and back and forth.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, no.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It had to be respect for my father.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And maybe he split it, I don't remember.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But I remember telling the story to my son.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "That's the only story that I ever told my oldest son-- or my youngest son-- what we went through in-- in the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I think he was so affected by this that in his speech for U-- UJA breakfast-- or it was maybe [NON-ENGLISH] that he told this-- this-- this story.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And this is the-- this is the way-- there were situations where the hunger had caused some people-- friends, relatives-- to steal from each other.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Here, I'm not trying to make myself a saint, but my father did the same thing for me.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We got a little bit of sugar, as I-- I noticed that my-- my portion was always a little more.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "He took from him and gave it to me.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And this was going on all along the time that we were together in the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And towards the end when he-- when he saved my life, and he gave his life for it.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So I don't know of any greater saint, of any finer person, of any dedicated father than my father was.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And I will never forgive the world for letting my children grow up without knowing a grandfather or a grandmother.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
